[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z] Option 1: Route with Freerouting (auto)
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]   The DSN file was exported during the build.
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]   From the repo root, run Freerouting:
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]     java -jar ~/.local/bin/freerouting-2.1.0.jar \
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]       -de projects/blue-dream-space/build/keyboard.dsn \
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]       -do projects/blue-dream-space/build/keyboard.ses -mp 50 -mt 24
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]   -mp  Max routing passes (default 50). Increase for complex boards,
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]         decrease to limit run time. There is no time-based timeout.
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]   -mt  Thread count for post-route optimization (your system: 24 cores).
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]         Note: the autoroute phase itself is always single-threaded.
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z] 
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]   Freerouting reads a freerouting.json config from its working directory.
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]   The build generates one at projects/blue-dream-space/build/freerouting.json with
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]   headless mode, via costs, and other router settings. To use it:
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]     cd projects/blue-dream-space/build && java -jar ~/.local/bin/freerouting-2.1.0.jar \
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z]       -de keyboard.dsn -do keyboard.ses -mp 50 -mt 24
[2026-03-27T19:17:20.765Z] 
